               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18460817-name-1424" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18460817-name-1424" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460817-name-1424" type="surname" value="M'LEISH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460817-name-1424" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>ANN M'LEISH</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a widow—the prisoner is my brother. On Wednesday morning, the 29th of July, he came to my place between four and five o'clock in the morning, and brought a basket and these articles—he left themand said he would call again in a few days—he staid about half an hour or three I quarters, and went away—I did not know what was in the basket before K went—the policemen came, and I let them have it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I came out from barracks, and was drinking at the I Swan; I then went to the Dorset Arms, and had a pint of beer; I went round the corner, took my stock off, and went to sleep; I awoke, and went into the road; I found the basket with these articles; I did not know what was in it.</p>
